divs: Sighting Details I was taking photos of the Orionide meteor shower between 4 and 6am...pics 86 to 91 show an object to the right of venus start out faint, get bright, and then fade out...they are 15 sec exposures, 1 has a meteorite in it...I'd like to find out what it is I photographed..at the time of shooting pics i did not notice object,not until viewing pics later on.. Location was Salisbury Beach Reservation,Massachusetts I have 7pics that illustrate the motion,but could only send three,I could email the rest if anyone is interested in answering my question...what is it? thank you for your time...

Summary: object flys in and out of sight
